text: This image displays a flow chart of the life-cycle of a t-shirt.     The background is white with grey arrows and text boxes.     The image displays ten grey boxes, with text inside each one.     The text boxes are arranged in a circle.     The first box, at the top of the circle, is labeled 'Raw Cotton Material', with an arrow pointing to the right.     The next box, to the right of 'Raw Cotton Material', is labeled 'Processing', with an arrow pointing to the right.     The next box, to the right of 'Processing', is labeled 'Manufacturing', with an arrow pointing down.     The next box, below 'Manufacturing', is labeled 'Packaging', with an arrow pointing to the left.     The next box, to the left of 'Packaging', is labeled 'Shipping', with an arrow pointing up.     The next box, above 'Shipping', is labeled 'Use', with an arrow pointing to the left.     The next box, to the left of 'Use', is labeled 'Reuse', with a double-sided arrow.     The next box, to the left of 'Reuse', is labeled 'Recycle', with an arrow pointing up.     The next and final box, above 'Recycle', is labeled 'Disposal', with an arrow pointing down.     The text inside each box is in a sans-serif font.     The image is a flow chart.
